<HEADLINE> Angolan Situation Develops in Favor of Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Situation of the the war-torn
Angola is developing in favor of the government, Kundi Paihama,
Angolan Defense Minister said here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the official National Radio of Angola, Paihama said
that the government forces "have won some victories recently", and
"the general situation is developing in favor of the government."
</P>
<P>
The defense minister mentioned especially a series of failures
in central Angola's Cunhinga City, on the side of the military
forces of the rebel National Union for the Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA).
</P>
<P>
About 130 UNITA men have been killed in the city, about 30 km
northwestern of Kuito, capital of Bie Province.
</P>
<P>
Paihama also mentioned the successful actions the government
forces launched in Huambo and its neighboring Caala City, where
about 30 UNITA men were killed on June 19 and a lot of ammunition
captured.
</P>
<P>
The offensive scheduled for the dry season, he said, has been
postponed for some complicated reasons, including military
training and logistic supply.
</P>
<P>
The government has once again refused demands from the
international community for talks with UNITA, saying that the
government is trying to end the conflict through military means in
the "last war" against UNITA in the dry season.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the government purchased a lot of weapons
in February for the decisive war.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
