<HEADLINE> Chinese Puppet Troupe Wins Warm Applause in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Some 800 Ethiopian audience
Sunday evening warmly applauded the excellent performance by the
visiting Chinese puppet troupe at the National Theatre in
Ethiopian Capital.
</P>
<P>
In his welcoming speech, Ethiopian Minister of Information and
Culture Woldemichael Chemu said the visit by the Chinese puppet
troupe "is a testimony to the consolidation of people to people
relations between our two sisterly countries".
</P>
<P>
He recalled that "a land mark in Ethio-Chinese relations was
observed during a state-to-state level visits to China by Prime
Minister Meles Zenawi, in 1995, and to Ethiopia of His Excellency
Jiang Zemin, President of the People's Republic of China, in
1996."
</P>
<P>
"These visits have a wider implication for the all rounded
relations of our two peoples and countries in the future," he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Ethiopia, Jiang Zhengyun, said that the
visit and performance by China's Chengdu Puppet Troupe will
further promote the friendly relationship of cultural cooperation
between China and Ethiopia, and enhance mutual understanding and
strengthen traditional friendship between the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Programs performed by the Chinese troupe included "Plating
Spinning", which borrows much from traditional Chinese acrobatics,
"Tortoise and Crane", which captures the humorous relations
between the two animals, and "Happy Spring Festival", which tells
how Chinese celebrate their traditional festival.
</P>
<P>
The one-hour performance won repeatedly warm applause from the
audience.
</P>
<P>
Puppet is a traditional Chinese art with a history of more than
2,000 years. This is the first visit to Africa by Chinese
puppeteers from Chengdu City in southwest China.
</P>
<P>
The 16-member Chinese troupe will give four performances
during its stay in Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia is the fifth country of the Chinese troupe's current
six-nation African tour, which include Zambia, Zimbabwe, Kenya,
Rwanda and Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
