<HEADLINE> Draft Ceasefire Agreement on Congo War Agreed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 27 (Xinhua) -- A draft ceasefire agreement was
completed Sunday at a officials meeting held in Zambian capital
over the past few days to make preparations for the Congo peace
summit.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Presidential Affairs Minister Erick Silwamba said here
Sunday that the draft agreement is now being considered by defense
ministers, foreign ministers and home affairs ministers of the
regional countries.
</P>
<P>
He said after the document is discussed by the ministers, the
regional summit will follow up.
</P>
<P>
The summit originally scheduled last Saturday was postponed.
</P>
<P>
At the summit, the ceasefire agreement and modalities to the
ceasefire will be signed by all the parties involved in the
11-month-old war in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC).
</P>
</TEXT>
