<HEADLINE> Iran, Turkmenistan Sign MOU on Drug Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Iran and Turkmenistan on Sunday
signed a memorandum of understanding on curbing drug and chemicals
trafficking along their joint borders.
</P>
<P>
The document was inked by Iranian Interior Minister Abdolvahed
Moussavi Lari and his Turkmen counterpart Pouran Berdiovich, the
Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Lari enumerated Iran's efforts in
fighting drug trafficking both on its borders and inland during
the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
He criticized the western governments for only offering lip
services and verbal agreements on combating drugs.
</P>
<P>
The Turkmen official expressed appreciation about Iran's
contribution to the drug fight in the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
