<HEADLINE> Arab Journalists, Lawyers Denounce Israeli Raids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Arab journalists and lawyers on
Sunday denounced Israel's attacks on Lebanese civilian targets as a
demonstration of the Jewish state's "terrorist orientation" and
"aggressive intentions" toward Arabs.
</P>
<P>
In a message to United Nations Secretary General Kofi Annan,
the Arab Journalists Union said Israel's attacks on Lebanese
civilian targets represented "a grave escalation not only against
Lebanon and its people, but the Arab nation as a whole."
</P>
<P>
The Cairo-based union called for "immediate intervention" by
the U.N. Security Council and implementation of the U.N.
resolution 425, which demands unconditional Israeli withdrawal
from Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
In retaliation for rocket attacks on its northern areas by
Lebanese Muslim guerrillas, Israel launched air strikes Thursday
night against power stations, bridges, roads and water plants near
Beirut, leaving eight people dead and at least 60 others wounded.
</P>
<P>
Arab journalists expressed confidence that "Israel's barbaric
attacks on" Lebanese civilian targets" will only strengthen the
determination" of the Lebanese resistance forces to "further its
legitimate struggle against the Israeli occupation."
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a so-called security zone in southern Lebanon in
1985 to allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border
attacks by Lebanese guerrillas. Lebanese resistance forces have
been fighting against the Israeli occupation troops since then.
</P>
<P>
The Arab Lawyers Union, meanwhile, called in a statement issued
in the day for convocation of an urgent Arab summit to seek ways
of forcing Israel to relinquish the occupied Arab lands.
</P>
<P>
The union urged the world community to declare solidarity with
the Lebanese people and compel Israel to carry out the U.N.
resolution unconditionally.
</P>
<P>
Arab lawyers called on the Arab countries to help Lebanon in
the reconstruction of the facilities shattered by Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
