<HEADLINE> Intern'l Agricultural Fair Opens in Novi Sad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Over 1,100 domestic and
international exhibitors will display their technical how-tos and
equipment of modern agriculture in a fair starting on Monday in
Novi Sad, capital city of Yugoslavia's northern province of
Voivodina.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural fair will coincide with two other exhibitions.
One of them is a building industry exhibition while still another
is the furniture and interior decoration fair.
</P>
<P>
The three exhibitions, to be held at the Novi Sad Fairgrounds,
are to close on July 4.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural exhibition is the first to have attracted
foreign exhibitors after NATO ended on June 8 the 11-week air
strikes against the Balkan country. 
</P>
