<HEADLINE> Iran Reiterates Support for Syria, Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Defense Minister Ali
Shamkhani said on Sunday that Iran's policy of supporting the
countries on the front-line of struggle against Israel is
"irrevocable."
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Syrian ambassador to Tehran Ahmad al-Hassan,
Shamkhani also pointed his fingers at what he called "certain
Palestinian groups" for "ignoring the interests, aspirations and
struggles of the Palestinian people and pinning their hope on a
compromise with Israel."
</P>
<P>
The meeting came after the Israeli air raids on Lebanon on
Thursday and Friday, which killed eight people and injured over 60
others.
</P>
<P>
Al-Hassan accused Israel of "trying to build up pressure on and
terrify the Lebanese government and people" by launching the
bloodiest Israeli air aggression on Lebanon in three years.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian diplomat praised Iran's "strong and explicit
stances" against the illegal acts of Israel and said that real
solidarity and cooperation in the Islamic world is the sole means
of encountering Israel's expansionism and defending Arab states'
legitimate rights.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi
arrived in Damascus on Sunday to discuss the Israeli attacks with
Syrian officials and show Tehran's support for Syria and Lebanon.
</P>
</TEXT>
