<HEADLINE> Tibetan Art Troupe Performing in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The China Tibetan Performing Arts
Troupe performed here this evening, following its shows in
Australia and New Zealand from June 11 to 26.
</P>
<P>
The performances included the Tibetan Monastery Suite "
Auspicious Nine Worlds", "Colorful Hada", and "Fluttering
Butterflies". Tseden Dolma, a famous singer, and her fellow
artists presented to the audience Tibetan songs and dances,
displays of clothing, and special instrument performance,
revealing Tibet's culture.
</P>
<P>
Chonpel, president of the Arts Troupe, said that they did a
good job in Australia and New Zealand where they gave six
performances to over 10,000 local people, helping them learn more
about Tibet.
</P>
<P>
The troupe was sent by the Chinese People's Association for
Friendship with Foreign Countries (CPAFFC).
</P>
<P>
A CPAFFC official who toured with the troupe said that the
artists' presentation touched audiences. According to him, an
official of the Australian Federal Parliament said that great
changes have taken place in Tibet, but some of the media have got
the wrong information.
</P>
<P>
The performance lasted an hour and a half and was greeted with
a great deal of applause.  
