<HEADLINE> Landmine Wounds 11 in Southwest Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Eleven persons were wounded when a
powerful anti- personnel mine exploded Monday outside a railway
storage in Vladikavkaz, capital of Russia's North Ossetia Republic,
the Interfax news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The victims, four in critical condition, were hospitalized in
the city that has witnessed a number of terrorist explosions in
the past year.
</P>
<P>
Nobody has claimed responsibility for the tragedy.
</P>
<P>
Four anti-personnel mines had been planted near a food stall
at the gate to the yard of the storage. One of them went off, but
the remaining three did not explode and were later defused by
soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Experts from the Interior Ministry and the Federal Security
Service are working at the site, Interfax said.
</P>
<P>
On March 19, around 60 people were killed and over 100 wounded
in a powerful blast at a Vladikavkaz market. 
</P>
