<HEADLINE> Chinese-aided Housing Project Launched in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The first Chinese-assisted housing
project in Viana Economic Development Zone in Angolan capital
Luanda was launched here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The project contracted by China's Jiangsu International
Corporation is worth some 11 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the project to be completed within 18 months, 195
flats of apartment houses with an area of 15,197 square meters
will be built.
</P>
<P>
Power and water supply systems, roads and green belts will also
be matched with the living compounds.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Luanda Jiang Yuande said at the launching
ceremony that the success of the project will improve the friendly
relations between the two nations and promote the bilateral
cooperation in other fields.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador said that China sincerely hopes Angola could end
the on- going conflict as soon as possible and embark on a road
toward peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Angolan Deputy Minister of Public Works and Urbanization
Antonio Gomas also said at the function that the project, with its
high standard, low cost and short time limit, is quite fit to the
situation in Angola.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese-assisted project has special implications on the
development of the capital city which is facing increasing
refugees and housing shortage, he noted. 
</P>
