<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 40th Anniversary Of Democratic Reforms Marked in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The regional government and
Communist Party Committee of the Tibet Autonomous Region held a
symposium here today on the 40th anniversary of the democratic
reforms in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
More than 300 representatives from all walks of life attended
the occasion and spoke highly of the remarkable changes that have
taken place in Tibet in the past four decades since the democratic
reforms and overthrow of the feudal surfdom in 1959.
</P>
<P>
The average life span of Tibetans has increased from 35.5 to 67
since then and Tibetans now account for 72.9 percent of the total
number of government officials in Tibet. Its GDP has grown 47-fold
and investment in fixed assets increased 468-fold during the
period.
</P>
<P>
The participants at the meeting pointed out that Tibet is at a
new starting point after 40 years of development and called for
uniting more closely around the CPC Central Committee with General
Secretary Jiang Zemin at the core and holding high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
