<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jordan's Population Exceeds 4.77 Million </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's population exceeded 4.77
million by the end of 1998, 570,000 more than the figure at the
end of 1995 when the last national census was conducted, according
to figures released by the National Statistics Bureau on Monday.
</P>
<P>
With a total number of 2.2 million, adults at or over the age
of 19 account for 46.4 percent of the total population,
indicating an increasing potential pressure on the labor market,
which has seen an annual unemployment rate of over 16 percent in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
Some 38.6 percent, or over 1.84 million of Jordanians are
living in the capital city of Amman, according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
The annual population growth rate of the desert kingdom stands
at 3.55 percent, among the highest in the world, due to the
absence of family planning measures.
</P>
<P>
Birth control remains a sensitive issue in the Muslim country
though the government complained the population pressure had
hindered the economic development of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
