<HEADLINE> Chinese Communist Party Has 61 Million Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Organization Department of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee reported today
that Party membership had grown to 61 million by the end of 1998,
or 5.1 percent of China's population.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, 10.29 million of the Party members
were females and 3.79 million were from ethnic minorities,
accounting for 16.6 percent and 6.1 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
There were 14.28 million, or 23.1 percent, Party members below
the age of 35, and 2.86 million, or 4.6 percent, below the age of
25.
</P>
<P>
There were 29.19 million who had graduated from high school or
equivalent institutes, 11.02 million who were college or
university grads, and 310,000 with graduate degrees, accounting
for 47.2 percent, 17.8 percent and 0.5 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Workers and farmers accounted for a hefty 48.8 percent of the
total Party members to 30.17 million, while some 7.88 million were
professionals or technicians, 5.57 million were cadres at
government organs, and 6.38 million were corporate managers.
</P>
<P>
There were 3.5 million grass-roots Party units, according to
the report.  
</P>
</TEXT>
