<HEADLINE> UAE Issues Order to Protect Ozone Layer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates (UAE)
issued an order on Monday to protect the ozone layer by regulating
the import and use of materials adversely affecting the layer.
</P>
<P>
The order, issued by Minister of Health and Chairman of the
Federal Environmental Agency (FEA) Hamad Rahman Al Madfa,
stipulates that authorized firms must obtain permission before
importing such materials, said the official WAM news agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency did not specify what those materials include.
</P>
<P>
According to FEA Director General Salem Al Dhahiri, the order
was in line with the Vienna Convention for the Protection of the
Ozone Layer, which was signed in 1985 and came into effect in
1988, and the Montreal Ozone Protection Protocol signed in 1987.
</P>
<P>
The FEA will hold a meeting with concerned organizations in
July to discuss the implementation of the order, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
