be the headquarters for services for the reconstruction of the
Balkans.
</P>
<P>
On his part, Bildt, who was former Swedish Premier and the
European Union's former Bosnia mediator, said that their talks
were aimed at preparing the ground for the New York talks and the
participation of countries which could play a significant role and
make an important contribution to the efforts for stability in
Kosovo and the wider Balkan region.
</P>
<P>
Greece was of those countries and could play a particularly
constructive role in the efforts under way to improve the
situation in Kosovo and the wide region, Bildt said.
</P>
