<HEADLINE> U.S. Urges Barak to Meet Arafat Before U.S. Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The United States has asked
Israeli Prime Minister-elect Ehud Barak to meet with Palestinian
leader Yasser Arafat prior to his upcoming trip to Washington, the
local media reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The White House request, delivered via the Israeli Embassy in
Washington, said U.S. President Bill Clinton wants to know whether
any new initiative to be put forward by Barak during his U.S. trip
will have been agreed upon by Arafat.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli Foreign Ministry refused to comment on the request,
but said it can only be decided by Barak himself whether to meet
with Arafat before going to Washington.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that after formation of his coalition
government, Barak will visit Washington in July to discuss with
Clinton on how to move the Middle East peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
Under the Israeli election law, Barak, who won the prime
ministerial election on May 17, has to form his coalition
government before July 9. 
</P>
