<HEADLINE> ARATS, SEF Officials Meet in Beijing Today </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Senior officials of the
Association of Relations Across the Taiwan Straits (ARATS) and
Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) said here today that their
meeting in Beijing was fruitful in implementing a four-point
consensus reached between the two sides in October 1998 and will
be conducive to further exchanges between them.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held between ARATS Deputy Secretary General Li
Yafei and his SEF counterpart Jan Jyh-horng.
</P>
<P>
The two discussed the time and place of a proposed Taiwan visit
by ARATS President Wang Daohan sometime this autumn. Wang's visit
is considered a continuation of the high-level talks between ARATS
and SEF which began last year.
</P>
<P>
Li repeated ARATS' two suggestions on dialogues between ARATS
and SEF about a joint forum on relations across the Taiwan Straits
and exchange of views on political obstacles in practical matters.
</P>
<P>
SEF made some suggestions about talks on returning hijackers
and illegal immigrants from the mainland and problems related to
fishing disputes.
</P>
<P>
Both agreed to increase exchanges this year and to organize law
and agriculture delegations during July and August.
</P>
<P>
Li said that ARATS hopes to cooperate with SEF in making
arrangements for cross-straits political and economic talks and
would like to hear SEF's opinion.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jincheng, ARATS' vice-president and secretary general,
also met with Jan today.
</P>
<P>
Jan is scheduled to leave Beijing for Taipei tomorrow morning.
</P>
</TEXT>
