<HEADLINE> Torrential Rain Hits Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai has had 539 mm of
precipitation as a result of the past five days' torrential rains,
which, according to local meteorologists, show no signs of letting
up.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rains have had a negative effect on agriculture in
the suburbs of Shanghai and have covered 3,113 hectares of
farmland with water.
</P>
<P>
The prices of fresh vegetables have gone up as a result,
according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The summer rain season came a little bit early this year,
starting on June 7, and the torrential rains hit in four
consecutive days earlier. 
</P>
