<HEADLINE> HK Exchange Fund Assets Decrease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary Authority
(HKMA) announced Monday that the total assets of the Exchange Fund
amounted to 927.6 billion HK dollars (118.9 billion U.S. dollars)
as at May 31, 1999.
</P>
<P>
According to HKMA figures, included in the Exchange Fund
Abridged Balance Sheet, the total assets of 927.6 billion HK
dollars were 28.1 billion HK dollars (3.6 billion U.S. dollars)
lower than at the end of April 1999.
</P>
<P>
Both foreign currency assets and Hong Kong dollar assets
decreased, by 5.6 billion HK dollars (700 million U.S. dollars)
and 22.5 billion HK dollars (2.9 billion U.S. dollars)
respectively.
</P>
<P>
An HKMA spokesperson said the reduction in foreign currency
assets reflected primarily revaluation effects on foreign currency
investments and redemption of currency notes issued, which were
partly offset by investment income from foreign currency
investments.
</P>
<P>
The decrease in Hong Kong dollar assets reflected mainly the
change in the market value of the Hong Kong equities held by the
Exchange Fund, the spokesperson explained. 
</P>
</TEXT>
