<HEADLINE> Syria Reiterates Death Penalties to Drug Dealers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Syria reiterated Monday that it
will punish drug dealers with death penalties.
</P>
<P>
The message was spelled out in an anti-drug symposium organized
by the Syrian Interior Ministry and the Syrian Society for the
Welfare of Prisoners and Their Families.
</P>
<P>
The symposium upheld the implementation of Law No. 2 passed in
1993, which considers drug addicts as patients, and supported the
death sentence on traffickers and smugglers of narcotics.
</P>
<P>
In June, Syrian authorities seized 40 kilograms of cocaine in
Tartous harbor and 12 kilograms of cocaine in Aleppo, according to
statements by Interior Minister Mohammad Harba at a meeting held
on the occasion of the World Day for the Combat of Narcotics on
June 26. 
</P>
