<HEADLINE> China Raising Standards for IT Industry (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the official, various companies are trying to sell
their specific standards for cellular telephones and digital TVs
in China so that they can penetrate and dominate the market here.
</P>
<P>
So China will focus on developing its own technical standards
in conjunction with patents. China will develop laser video
standards, for example, which are compatible with DVD standards.
</P>
<P>
Once the standards are set, foreign products have to be
compatible with them if they want to enter the Chinese market, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Lu said that the Ministry of Information Industry will
carefully time the approval of certain technical standards to
leave adequate time and room for the local IT industry to grow.
</P>
<P>
According to him, China will reform the technical standards on
a trial basis this year and will set up a nationwide commission on
standardizing audio, video, and multimedia systems and equipment,
which will consider all interested groups like the government,
enterprises, and research institutes to encourage the corporate
world and consumers to play a major role in drafting technical
standards.  
</P>
