<HEADLINE> China's Communist Party Celebrates 78th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today urged Party leaders at different levels to continue the
current drive for theoretical study, political awareness, and good
conduct.
</P>
<P>
At a forum in Beijing's Great Hall of the People for the 78th
anniversary of the Communist Party of China (CPC), Jiang, who is
also general secretary of the CPC Central Committee, pointed to
the positive results of this education drive in the past several
months and asked that the drive be continued to build the CPC.
</P>
<P>
He reviewed the CPC's history and emphasized that its success
came from the Party's ideological, political, organizational, and
workstyle efforts.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the question of how to improve the building
of the CPC in times of peace has always been a major issue and the
present education drive is an innovative approach to this.
</P>
<P>
He said that political awareness should focus on Marxism and
socialism with Chinese characteristics and on the fundamental
interests of the people. Political awareness exists in economic
work and various other undertakings and leaders should be able to
observe or handle various issues from a political point of view.
</P>
<P>
Theoretical study is also very important, he said, adding that
leaders should master Marxist theories well, gain other knowledge,
keep a sharp eye on different ideas, and be able to correctly
design policies and measures.
</P>
<P>
For education in good conduct, Jiang said, leaders at different
levels need to carry forward the political nature and
revolutionary integrity of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
The forum was chaired by Hu Jintao, a member of the Standing
Committee of the Political Bureau of CPC Central Committee, was
attended by many senior CPC leaders.  
</P>
