<HEADLINE> Rainstorms And Heatwave Hit China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Rainstorms have hit many areas on
the middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River, while a
heatwave has been sweeping across north China.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Meteorology Station, from 5:00 a.m.
June 25 to 5:00 a.m. today, as much as 80 mm of rain has fallen on
parts of Jiangsu, Anhui, Zhejiang, and Jiangxi provinces in the
East and on parts of Hubei and Hunan provinces in central China.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the rainstorms have also hit parts of Guizhou,
Sichuan, and Yunnan provinces, the city of Chongqing, and the
Guangxi Zhuang and Tibet autonomous regions in southwest China.
all of the affected areas are along the Yangtze.
</P>
<P>
Some regions received as much as 200 mm of rain during the
period.
</P>
<P>
While heavy rains are rampaging central, east and southwest
China, a heatwave has swept north China's Hebei and Shanxi
provinces and the cities of Beijing and Tianjin since June 24,
with temperature running around 35 to 37 degrees centigrade.
</P>
<P>
The weather forecast is for rain to continue along the Yangtze
and Huai rivers, but decreasing a bit. And Hebei and Shanxi can
expect temperatures to continue in the range of 34-36 degrees.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
