<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990628.0090 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Shares Ride Higher on Strong Resource Stock </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Australian shares closed firmer
Monday after a rally in resource stocks inspired rises in the
broader market.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index ended 30.3 points higher at 2,990.3,
underpinned by the all resources index's 33.6-point gain to
1,221.3.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index was also higher with a 35-point rise
to 5,223.3 points.
</P>
<P>
Diversified miner BHP was also strong with a 70-cent jump to
17.6 Australian dollars and global miner Rio Tinto climbed 91.8
cents to 25.268 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
But the enthusiasm for base metals stocks bypassed most of the
gold sector after bullion gave up 1.8 U.S. dollars to be trading
at 259.3 U.S. dollars late in the day.
</P>
<P>
Overall turnover figures showed that 462.53 million shares
traded for 733.26 million U.S. dollars, with 646 rising stocks,
634 falling ones and 457 steady.
</P>
<P>
Bank stocks were also positive, the only dark spot being
National Australia Bank (NAB) which ended lower after it began
trading on an ex-dividend basis Monday.
</P>
<P>
NAB closed 29.6 cents down at 24.94 Australian dollars, Westpac
bank climbed 30 cents to 10.01 Australian dollars, ANZ bank
improved 26.1 cents to 11.341 Australian dollars and the
Commonwealth Bank of Australia added 23 cents to reach 24.48
Australian dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
