<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Drifts to Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar drifted
Monday to end at 66.06 U.S. cents from Friday's close of 66.27
U.S. cents, after reaching a high of 66.33 U.S. cents during
morning trade.
</P>
<P>
MMS Standard &AMP; Poor's currency strategist Alex Douglas said the
local unit was caught between concern about the May trade deficit
data to be made public this week and any lift it might gain from
higher copper prices.
</P>
<P>
"(There's some) buying interest on firmer base metals (prices),
especially copper, which rose again on Friday night," he said.
</P>
<P>
Also at the close in Sydney, the Australian currency was
trading at 0.6339 euro from 0.6355 euro on Friday and at 79.5
Japanese yen from 80.59 yen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
