<HEADLINE> Old Industrial Base Gives Technology A Kick Start </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The northeastern Chinese province
of Liaoning, an old heavy industrial base, has increased its
financial input into the technological upgrading of state
enterprises this year to spur on the provincial economy.
</P>
<P>
Investment in technological projects totaled 2.26 billion yuan
(272 million US dollars) during the first four months, up 10.2
percent from the same period last year. Liaoning expects such
investment to hit 28 billion yuan this year, an increase of 7.1
percent over 1998.
</P>
<P>
The provinces has listed a total of 189 technological
renovation projects for the Ninth Five Year Plan (1996-2000), and
101 projects have been kicked start with a total investment of 31.
54 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
"Intensified investment is necessary to reform the traditional
industries in Liaoning, and to restructure the economy of this old
industrial base," said Zhang Guoguang, governor of Liaoning.
</P>
<P>
The province is expected to launch another 20 key technological
renovation projects this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
