<HEADLINE> BOC Launches Internet Banking Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The Bank of China (BOC) announced
today that it has launched a range of Internet banking services
providing its customers with online shopping facilities.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president of the BOC, Hua Qingshan said that this will
enable BOC customers to conduct online inquiries, account
transfers, payments, settlements and other business.
</P>
<P>
He said that the BOC had introduced the state of the art Secure
Electronic Transaction model in designing its Internet services,
in a bid to ensure the security of online payments and shopping.
</P>
<P>
According to Hua, these services include Corporate Online
Financing, Internet Payments and Bank-Securities Express.
</P>
<P>
The Corporate Online Financing provides corporate customers
with online account inquiries, corporate internal transfer of
accounts, statements on international income and expenditure and
other services.
</P>
<P>
The Internet Payment Service enables individual customers to do
online shopping using the Great Wall Charge Card issued by the BOC,
while Bank-Securities Express is specially designed for securities
firms to conduct capital clearing businesses.
</P>
<P>
"Boasting the most advanced Internet security measures, these
new services can ensure the safety of card holders' trading
information," Hua said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
