<HEADLINE> hke062843 - Pak Concerned over Disappearance of Diplomat in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Monday expressed its
concern over the "mysterious disappearance" of Dil Fayyaz, a
diplomat of its High Commission in New Delhi, since Sunday and
called for his immediate release.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan has "conveyed a demarche to the Indian High Commission
this morning" over Fayyaz's disappearance, said a statement of the
Ministry of Foreign Affairs here.
</P>
<P>
Fayyaz is missing since 18:00 local time Sunday (13:00 GMT)
when he left for the railway station.
</P>
<P>
The Indian Deputy High Commissioner was summoned to Foreign
Office here on Monday and was "reminded of the responsibility of
the government of India to ensure the safety and security of
Pakistan High Commission officials."
</P>
<P>
"It was also conveyed that in this case of kidnapping of
Pakistan High Commission's official, the Indian government must
make every effort to trace his whereabouts and secure his
immediate release," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It said, if the Pakistani official has been "taken into custody
by Indian security agencies, he should be released forthwith and
treated in accordance with the established norms."
</P>
<P>
The Pakistan High Commission in New Delhi has also raised this
matter with the Indian Ministry of External Affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
