<HEADLINE> 30 Nigerians Killed in Road Accidents in Lagos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Some 30 people were killed in two
road accidents in Nigeria's commercial hub Lagos in the past two
days, the Daily Times newspaper reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
At least 15 persons were dead and several others injured in an
accident involving the popular "molue" bus and a trailer on the
Apapa-Oshodi Expressway near Lagos.
</P>
<P>
The accident victims died on the spot when the bus and trailer
had a head-on-collision. Some of the bodies were said to have been
mangled, according to the paper.
</P>
<P>
The tragedy came on the heels of a similar one in which another
15 persons were killed at the outskirts of Lagos Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Road Safety Commission said in an earlier report
that over 35,460 traffic accidents had occurred during the past
two decades in Lagos, averaging 10 daily, killing a total of about
7,284 people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
