<HEADLINE> Uganda the Surprise in African Zone Olympic Qualifiers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Uganda became the only
unseeded side to reach the final phase of the 2000 Olympic
qualifying tournament in Africa by scraping through on away goals
rule.
</P>
<P>
Uganda suffered a 1-2 away defeat to Zambia in the return leg
this weekend, but that was enough to see them through after their
1-0 home win.
</P>
<P>
They join defending champions Nigeria, Angola and Mauritius or
Zimbabwe in Group One with the top finishers guaranteed a place at
the 16-team finals in Australia next September.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria advanced 6-3 on aggregate after losing 3-2 in Namibia
on the weekend, while Angola cruised through with a 4-0 victory in
Botswana.
</P>
<P>
The Mauritius-Zimbabwe match on the Indian Ocean island of
Reunion did not take place and spokesman Dr Viken Djizmedjian said
the African Football Confederation were investigating.
</P>
<P>
The Group Two was led by Ghana, who defeat Tanzania 2-1 to
advance on 3-1 aggregate. They will be joined by Cameroon, Guinea
and South Africa, who managed a 1-0 home win over Togo to progress
3-2 on aggregate.
</P>
<P>
The Group Three features Tunisia, Cote d'Ivoire, Egypt and
Morocco.
</P>
<P>
Group winners qualify for finals in Australia. The best group
runners-up playoff against Oceania winners between March 17 and
May 15 for another place. 
</P>
</TEXT>
