<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 46.90 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Monday closed at 4,158.67 as
against last Friday's close of 4,111.77, netting a gain of 46.90
points or 1.14 percent.
</P>
<P>
The national index also advanced by 25.03 points to 1,794.92
from the previous close of 1,769.89.
</P>
