<HEADLINE> Malawi's New Cabinet Named </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Malawian President Bakili Muluzi
Sunday appointed a new 28-member cabinet of 20 ministers and eight
deputies, retaining most of his former cabinet, the Malawi News
Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Muluzi has given a post of minister for president affairs to
former speaker of parliament, Rodwell Munyenyembe while
reappointing Aleke Banda and Cassim Chilumpha as Agriculture
Minister and Finance Minister respectively.
</P>
<P>
Former Minister of Education, Sports and Culture Brown
Mpinganjira has become Minister of Foreign Affairs. Ken Lipenga
took the portfolio left by Mpinganjira.
</P>
<P>
The post of Minister of Home Affairs has gone to Patrick Mbewe
who was formerly the minister of tourism.
</P>
<P>
Muluzi has also appointed two full women ministers and two
women deputies from a list of the 16 lady members of parliament.
</P>
<P>
The ministers featured in the new cabinet are from all the
three regions of the southern African country. 
</P>
