<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 55.78
points, or 0.4 percent, to close at 13,840.29 in cautious trade
Monday while China's plays chalked up remarkable gains backed by
the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
The market turnover decreased by 1.561 billion HK dollars (200
million U.S. dollars) from the Friday session to 6.656 billion HK
dollars (853 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Sub-index Utilities, Properties, and Commerce &AMP; Industry all
registered gains of 1.52 percent, 1.33 percent and 0.47 percent
respectively, but Finance dropped by 0.92 percent.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares gained remarkably as the Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index and the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corporations
Index scored increases of 3.48 percent and 3.59 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The share prices fell 16.34 points, or 0.12 percent, to open at
13,768.17 Monday and finished the morning session at 13,820.86.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng index rose 4.39 points, or 0.03 percent, to close
last week's trade at 13,784.51 Friday. 
