<HEADLINE> Retail Sales Industry Brisk in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The retail sales volume in south
China's Guangdong Province rose by 8.7 percent on a yearly basis
in the first five months of this year, reaching 144.73 billion
yuan.
</P>
<P>
The increase in retail sales shows that the province's economy
is growing on a fast and steady track, local authorities said.
</P>
<P>
In May, Guangdong's retail sales represented a year on year
increase of 9.9 percent, 4.6 percentage points more than the
national average.
</P>
<P>
The province adopted the policy of stimulating domestic demand
to invigorate the market, especially the rural market. According
to statistics, retail sales in the province's rural areas
increased 10.3 percent, 2.2 percentage points more than that of
urban areas. 
</P>
