<HEADLINE> Northeast China City to Host agricultural Fairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Shenyang, capital of northeast
China's Liaoning Province, is to host a series of trade fairs on
agriculture, flowers and vegetables in August-October, according
to sources from the provincial government.
</P>
<P>
Shenyang has nearly eight agricultural counties, 682,900
hectares of farmland and 1.5 million people are engaged in
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The agriculture exhibition fair, which will be held from August
25-28, is aimed at displaying the province's agricultural
achievements, promote interprovincial commodity exchanges and
provide a chance to introduce overseas high-tech developments.
</P>
<P>
The flower trade fair will be hosted during September 5 to
October 9. The fair is themed developing the domestic and
international market for the flower industry. At the same time,
the fair will display exhibits of fresh flowers, potted plants,
various cacti species, dry flowers, silk flowers and rare stones.
</P>
<P>
The North China Vegetable Fair, the first of its kind, is to be
hosted here in September-October. It is aimed at setting up a
vegetable marketing and sales network in China and northeast Asia
with Shenyang as the center. 
</P>
</TEXT>
