<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Smooth Development of Real Estate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- China's real estate index, which
is a pointer to the industry's health, reached 103.28 in May this
year, up 1.92 points from the same month in 1998, indicating that
it still operates in a "favorable" climate, an official report
said today.
</P>
<P>
Jointly issued by the National Bureau of Statistics and the
China Business Climate Monitoring Center, the report admitted that
the figure is 0.38 points lower than that in April, marking a
downward development trend.
</P>
<P>
In May, the acreage of land development, the investment in real
estate, the acreage of newly started projects and the housing
prices increased by a large margin, stimulating rapid development
of the industry.
</P>
<P>
In January-May period, the sector developed 17 million square
meters of land, up 82.8 percent over the same period last year,
indicating a booming potential for the industry.
</P>
<P>
The investment in the industry also increased by 21.3 percent
on a year on year basis to reach 94.7 billion yuan for the period,
according to the statistics.
</P>
<P>
The report admitted that some other indices, such as that for
the acreage of completed real estate projects and lands sales as
well as for deposits of funds had decreased somewhat.
</P>
<P>
In the past five months, 22.97 million sq. meters of houses
were built, up 32.8 percent on a year on year basis but the growth
rate is still lower than that in the January-April period, said
the report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
