<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading French newspapers on Monday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- Weakened by the European election two weeks ago, France's
Gaullist party, the Rally for the Republic (RPR), has designated a
team to decide its reconstruction program and will elect its new
general secretary by the end of 1999 to replace Nicolas Sarkoz,
who has resigned after the European election. The breaking away of
a group of RPR politicians led by former Interior Minister Charles
Pasqua has made the survival of RPR more difficult.
</P>
<P>
-- French troops deployed in Mitrovica, northern Kosovo,
intervened on Saturday to stop a confrontation between Serbs and
Albanians, now separated by a demarcation line along the Ibri
river which cuts the city into two parts. The Albanians tried
cross the river in a peaceful demonstration against the Serbs. The
Serbs denounced it as a provocation by the Kosovo Liberation Army.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The Gaullist Rally for the Republic remains divided over its
reconstruction program presented by the party's general secretary
Nicolas Sarkozy. Two weeks after the failure of RPR in the
European election, Sarkozy hopes to fix the program for
reconstructing the party at its congress in October, before the
election of the party's new general secretary.
</P>
<P>
-- The first summit meeting of leaders of European Union (EU)
countries and Latin America will open on Monday in Rio de Janeiro.
As the result of a French proposal, the Rio Summit should lay the
first stone of a free trade union between EU and South American
nations, to start with the Mercosur member countries. 
</P>
