<HEADLINE> Construction of China's First Bonded Dock Underway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Construction of China's first
bonded dock is underway at the Port of Tianjin, the biggest in
north China.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, a duty-free zone is also being built inside
the Tianjin Binhai Airport, which is not far from the Tianjin
Bonded Zone.
</P>
<P>
According to officials, the dock will enable cargoes to
directly enter the Tianjin Bonded Zone, and the airport duty-free
zone will provide more rapid air transportation service for the
enterprises in the Zone.
</P>
<P>
Local experts also point out that the Tianjin Bonded Zone will
thus become the country's first duty-free region having access to
cargo transportation by air, land and sea.  
</P>
