<HEADLINE> Double-Track Section of Beijing-Kowloon Railway Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The southern double-track section
of the Beijing-Kowloon Railway was opened to traffic today, two
days ahead of schedule.
</P>
<P>
The 609 km double-track section, including 252 bridges, links
Xiangtang, east China's Jiangxi Province, with Longchuan in south
China's Guangdong Province,
</P>
<P>
The section is expected to increase the annual cargo volume for
the Beijing-Kowloon Railway from 11 million tons to 21 millions
tons, and the number of passenger trains passing each way daily
from nine to 15.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the section commenced in September 1998 and
cost a total of 2.3 billion yuan (277 million US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
