<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cargo Plane Overshoots Runway in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 28 (Xinhua) - A cargo plane coming from Subic
overshot the runway upon landing at the Ninoy Aquino International
Airport Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
However, neither of the two pilots was reported hurt in the
accident, which involved an Airbus 310 and affected the flight
operations at the premier airport, causing heavy losses to the
government, the Philippines News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
According to the initial investigation, the accident was
believed to have been due to the pilots' error.
</P>
<P>
The airport authority said the aircraft's pilots had been
warned by the control tower to slow down because the plane was
moving too fast while it was about to land.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft had its wings and one of its two engines
destroyed. So far, about 15 international commercial flights have
been affected by the accident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
