<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Residents Keen to Buy Housing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Residents in Shanghai, China's
leading industrial and commercial city, are now keen to buy
housing, especially economical apartments, according to a recent
survey.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by the Shanghai Branch of the Industrial
and Commercial Bank of China, shows that more than 80 percent of
910 respondents have plans to buy housing within one or two years.
</P>
<P>
About 51 percent of the surveyed say they will purchase
apartments measuring 80 to 100 square meters each, and some 54
percent say they can afford prices of 3,000 to 5,000 yuan per
square meter.
</P>
<P>
As to the source of funding, more than 40 percent of the
respondents say they will use housing loans from banks.
</P>
<P>
Analysts point out that the survey indicates good prospects for
the development of the local real estate market which has been
sluggish for a few years.
</P>
<P>
All commercial banks in Shanghai have opened individual housing
loan services this year. The Shanghai Branch of the Industrial and
Commercial Bank of China alone has already lent 1.57 billion yuan
in such loans.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
