</P>
<P>
The cooperation will cover information, administration,
planning, budget, legal affairs, logistics, personnel and
education.(Albania-Czech-Military)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PYONGYANG -- General-Secretary Kim Jong Il of the Workers'
Party of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has called for
concerted efforts to develop agriculture and ensure harvest this
year, newspaper reports said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Kim said that agriculture is the most important front in
solving the food, clothing and housing problems of the people and
all the people should concentrate their efforts on farming in
order to bring about a bumper harvest this year.(DPRK-Kim-
Agriculture)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Philippines will press the World Trade
Organization (WTO) to implement an agreement that would phase out
export quotas on textiles and clothing products, Manila Bulletin
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
This concern will form part of the government's "policy
statement" in relation to the 1999 trade policy review of the
Philippines in the WTO, the report said.
</P>
<P>
In a memorandum, the nation's chief trade negotiator Edsel
Custodio said that developed countries have mainly chosen to delay
the removal of quotas from the coverage of textiles and clothing
products from the multilateral trading system (MTS) of the WTO.(
Philippines-Export Quota)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
COLOMBO -- The second Asian Mayors' Forum was inaugurated
Monday here by Sri Lankan Minister of Provincial Councils and
Local Government Alavi Moulana.
</P>
<P>
"With the increasing trend of urbanization, Asian countries are
going to face many challenges relating to the adequate and
effective delivery of municipal services," Minister Moulana told
the opening ceremony.(Sri Lanka-Asian Mayors )
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Seventy-four international volunteers arrived in
Dili, capital of East Timor, via special flights from Darwin,
Australia, on Monday to help conduct the territory's August direct
ballot, the Antara News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
"The volunteers will be immediately posted in all districts of
East Timor to carry out their jobs, such as conducting the
registration of voters and making preparations for polling
stations," said David Wimhurst, spokesman of the United Nations
Assistance Mission in East Timor (UNAMET). (Indonesia-East Timor-
Voluteers)
</P>
