<DOCNO> XIE19990628.0147 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnamese City's GDP Up 5.6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, June 28 (Xinhua) -- The gross domestic product of Ho Chi
Minh City in Vietnam reached 21.703 trillion Vietnamese dong
(1.563 billion U.S. dollars), in the first half of this year, 5.6
percent higher than a year ago, according to Vietnam's official
news agency VNA.
</P>
<P>
Eighteen out of the 26 industries in Ho Chi Minh City,
Vietnam's biggest economic hub, recorded year-on-year increases in
output value and seven others saw falls in production value. High
growth rates were seen in food processing, chemicals, rubber and
plastic goods.
</P>
<P>
The centrally-run sector contributed 8.49 trillion dong (about
610 million dollars), 5-percent more than the same period of last
year.
</P>
<P>
The locally-run sector in the first six months grossed 7.108
trillion dong (511.4 million dollars) in industrial output value,
3.3 percent higher than a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-invested enterprises in the same period achieved a
production value of 6.279 trillion dong (451.7 million dollars), a
year-on-year increase of 21 percent. The city now has about 300
operational foreign invested enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The city in the past six months attained an export-import value
of 2 billion dollars or a 10.2-percent year-on-year increase. The
city's import value meanwhile reached 1.734 billion dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
