<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 22 Tamil Rebels Killed in Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
killed 22 Tamil rebels Sunday in separate clashes in Northern
Province, the Defense Ministry announced here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Government troops Sunday morning engaged and killed four Tamil
rebels in the south of Muppankulam town. In another incident
southwest of the town on the same day, troops engaged a group of
rebels, killing one terrorist and injuring eight others, Military
Spokesman Rp Witana said.
</P>
<P>
He said Tamil rebels fired mortars at government troops in the
east of Periyamadu on the same. The troops retaliated with mortars
and artillery, killing eight rebels. One soldier was killed and
three others injured during the fighting.
</P>
<P>
On the same day in southwest Wanni, rebels attacked the forward
defense line of the newly captured area. The troops repulsed the
attack using mortars and artillery and recovered the dead bodies
of seven terrorists along with some weapons. One soldier was
killed and five others were injured in the incident, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
In another incident on the same day, troops killed two rebels
and injured another, Witana added.
</P>
<P>
Tamil rebels have been fighting the Sri Lankan government since
1983 for an independent Tamil homeland in the north and east of
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
