<DOCNO> XIE19990628.0152 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Residents Relocated Before Flood Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 28 (Xinhua) -- A total of 57,700 residents
living in the reservoir area of the Xiaolangdi Water Control
Project, the second largest under construction after the Three
Gorges Project, have been relocated ahead of the expected flooding
season.
</P>
<P>
As the largest water control project on the Yellow River, China
's second longest, the Xiaolangdi project is designed to protect
the areas of the lower reaches of the Yellow River from flooding.
The project calls for relocation of nearly 200,000 residents in
central China's Henan and north China's Shanxi provinces, and 27,
233 ha of land is to be submerged within the reservoir area.
</P>
<P>
With the flood season approaching, all the residents living 215
meters below the expected waterline will have to move to higher
land to avoid problems during the flood season.
</P>
<P>
Governments at all levels in Henan and Shanxi have taken a
series of measures to speed up the relocation work, including
allocating new lots of land for the residents, and ensuring
sufficient funding for the relocation project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
