<HEADLINE> Car Incident Kills 20 in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Twenty passengers were killed and
27 others injured in northern Iran on Sunday afternoon when a bus
plunged from a bridge.
</P>
<P>
The bus was on its way from Qouchan in northern Khorasan
province to Shiraz in southern Fars province when the accident
occurred in Damghan in the northern province of Seman, some 250
kilometers east of Tehran, the Islamic Republic News Agency
reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen women and six men and children were killed and the
injured passengers were rushed to hospitals and the Red Crescent
centers in the cities nearby, the news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Highway traffic experts said the steep road, negligence of the
driver in noticing traffic signs and high speed were reasons
behind the incident.
</P>
<P>
Last Monday, 21 people were killed and six others seriously
injured in the central province of Isfahan when a passenger bus
collided with a truck.
</P>
<P>
Iranian traffic officials have complained that the number of
traffic incidents in Iran is about 200 percent of the
average in the world. 
</P>
</TEXT>
