<HEADLINE> Egypt, Spain to Seek Economic, Trade Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 28 (Xinhua) -- A joint committee will soon seek
further cooperation between Egypt and Spain in industry, trade,
investment and science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian economic sources said that the two sides will discuss
the possibility of setting up a joint business council when the
Egyptian-Spanish Higher Committee meets in the first half of
September in Madrid, Spain, the Egyptian Gazette newspaper
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
The business council is aimed at balancing the bilateral trade
by expanding trade volume, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show that trade volume stood at 450 million
U.S. dollars between Egypt and Spain in 1998, with Egypt exporting
goods worth 92 million dollars, the pro-government newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said an agreement on prevention of dual taxation
and several accords on trade cooperation will be signed between
the two countries during the committee session.
</P>
<P>
Spain has agreed to sponsor two conferences in Madrid and
Barcelona on the sidelines of the committee meetings, which are
aimed at encouraging Spanish investment in Egypt, the sources
added.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of Egyptian businessmen is expected to take part
in both conferences, during which the businessmen will highlight
the fields of investment in their country.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian government is stepping up efforts to attract
foreign businessmen to buy state-run enterprises chosen for
privatization and invest in its industrial free zones and national
project, such as Toshka in the south, which is implemented to
reclaim desert land.
</P>
<P>
Spain has so far set up 15 joint ventures in Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
