<HEADLINE> Northeast China Province Exports Bounce Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua)-- Northeast China's Liaoning Province
exported 2.6 billion U.S. dollars worth of goods in January-May,
up 4.5 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
An official from this heavy industry base said that Liaoning
has seen a month by month increase in exports, thanks to the
diminishing influences of the Asian financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The province exported 1.12 billion U.S. dollar worth of
machinery and electronic products in the five months, up 21.1
percent on a yearly basis. The province's machinery and
electronics exports accounted for nearly 40 percent of the
provincial total.
</P>
<P>
In the five months, Liaoning's export to Japan, the Republic of
Korea and Southeast Asia rose 10.8 percent, 17.9 percent and 7.9
percent respectively over the same period last year.  
</P>
