<HEADLINE> Chinese Subway Opens For Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 28 (Xinhua)-- The new subway in Guangzhou,
capital of south China's Guangdong Province, became operational
today.
</P>
<P>
At a cost of 12.7 billion yuan (1.53 billion US dollars) the
Line No.1 subway runs for 18.48 km and has 16 stations.
</P>
<P>
Construction began in December 1993 and is expected to carry
100,000 people ever day, alleviating 15 percent of the city's
transport burden.
</P>
<P>
Trains run at 35 km per hour compared with only nine km for an
average bus in the city. 
</P>
