<HEADLINE> African Trade Workshop To Be Held in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 28 (Xinhua) -- A workshop on developing
African trade will be held in South Africa Tuesday to promote
participation of African states in international trade
negotiations, the Organization of African Unity (OAU) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The workshop should assist African countries in identifying
trade issues of priority interests to them that need to be
advanced or defended in international trade negotiations", said an
OAU press release issued here.
</P>
<P>
"In this way, African countries can enhance their preparedness
for proactive and effective participation in the Third World Trade
Organization Ministerial Conference in Seattle, USA," it added.
</P>
<P>
The four-day workshop is organized by the United Nations
Conference on Trade and Development (UNCTAD) in collaboration with
the OAU, the African Economic Community (AEC) and the government
of South Africa.
</P>
<P>
It is one of three positive agenda of regional and
inter-regional workshops planned respectively in Asia, Africa and
Latin America and the Caribbean as mandated by the United Nations
General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
According to the OAU press release, the workshop would bring
together senior government trade experts and negotiators from
African and other developing countries.
</P>
<P>
They will discuss and recommended general and sectoral trade
policy issues which African countries need to pursue at different
trade negotiation fora in a coherent and consistent manner to
achieve the best results for these countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
