<HEADLINE> Ningxia Speeds Up Basic Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Ningxia Hui
Autonomous Region has invested nearly 500 million yuan (60 million
US dollars) to build a batch of technical renovation projects and
basic facilities in the first five months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The investment amount was 2.2 times that of the same period of
last year.
</P>
<P>
Work has begun on 12 key projects, including the expansion of
the Qingtongxia aluminum plant, the construction of the Guyaozi-
Wangquanliang high-grade highway, an afforestation project in the
eastern part of the Helan Mountain and the upgrading of urban and
rural electricity networks, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
The region will build 15 basic construction projects this year.
The effort will help optimize the investment and economic
structures in Ningxia and give a shot in the arm to the region's
economic growth through the stimulation of domestic demand,
officials added.  
</P>
