<HEADLINE> Contracted Foreign Investment Approaches 600 Billion US Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 28 (Xinhua) -- China had approved the
establishment of 331,024 overseas-funded enterprises by the end of
last May, the International Business Daily reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Contracted overseas investment in China had reached 587.1
billion U.S. dollars while actual used investment had amounted to
281.4 billion U.S. dollars by then, according to statistics from
the Chinese Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
During May this year, China made use of a total of 3.7 billion
U.S. dollars, up 15.59 percent than the same period of last year,
the first growth this year.
</P>
<P>
In the first five months of this year, China approved the
setting up of 6,312 new overseas-funded enterprises, down 13.63
percent. The contracted investment totaled 14.5 billion U.S.
dollars and actual used investment reached 13.9 billion U.S.
dollars, down 17.04 percent and 6.6 percent respectively.
</P>
