assuming office in late 1981, he has pursued efforts to invigorate
the Egyptian economy and build infrastructure facilities.
</P>
<P>
Al-Akhbar:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Minister of Culture Farouq Hosni will Tuesday give
the go-ahead for a massive operation to retrieve the sunken naval
pieces of Nepoleon's fleet in the Mediterranean. The sunken pieces
are remnants of the fleet which was vanquished almost 200 years
ago after the failure of the French campaign on Egypt.
</P>
<P>
Al-Gomhuria:
</P>
<P>
-- Egyptian Ministry of Rural Development will organize the
first exhibition of hand-made items and products of cottage
industries in Kigali, Rwanda, on July 1-8.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is expected to open new markets for the Egyptian
exports in Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian Gazette:
</P>
<P>
-- The Egyptian Exports Development Center will sponsor a
symposium on July 1 to boost Afro-Arab trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Mohamed Hamdi Salem, chairman of the center, said that
representatives from 25 Egyptian companies will leave Monday for
Kenya and Zambia to market Egyptian products.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, business delegations have
been sent to Kenya, Uganda and Italy to seek new markets. In Kenya
and Uganda, deals worth 14 million U.S. dollars were concluded.
</P>
