<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Service Industry Keen on ISO Certificates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 28 (Xinhua) -- China's service industry is
becoming more aware of the need to obtain quality certificates
granted by the Organization for International Standardization.
</P>
<P>
People from the sector had formerly overlooked the necessity to
acquire the internationally-acknowledged certificate, because many
considered that it only affected those conducting foreign trade.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Quality Certification Center for Import
and Export Commodities (CQC), over 7,000 Chinese firms have set up
ISO9000 quality systems and won certification, since the system
was introduced in 1992.
</P>
<P>
Most of the companies are actually within the manufacturing
industries, especially those involved in foreign trade but as the
service sector gets bigger, it is facing a higher demand for
efficiency and quality, on which the ISO system offers a standard.
</P>
<P>
Entrepreneurs from the sector in south China's Guangdong
Province, Hong Kong and Macao recently convened in this provincial
capital to exchange ideas about the ISO9000 quality system in
order to help firms to modernize their management, increase
efficiency and guarantee the quality of their services.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from a Bank of China's local office which is
the first service industry company to obtain ISO certification in
China, said that the bank has developed better inter-department
cooperation after the system was introduced.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
