<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU, Latin American Ministers Preparing for Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministers from the
European Union (EU), Latin America and the Caribbean held a
preparatory meeting here Sunday for the upcoming June 28-29 summit.
</P>
<P>
The ministers re-examined the major topics to be discussed and
the documents to be signed during the summit, said Uruguayan
Foreign Minister Didier Opertti who attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
They agreed on a political document "The Rio Declaration" and a
plan of action which urges the EU and Latin America to strengthen
their economic cooperation in the next century, especially in the
field of establishing free trade zones, Opertti said.
</P>
<P>
During the Rio summit, the heads of state and government will
discuss the possibility of free trade and try to solve their
differences on such issues as farm subsidies.
</P>
<P>
However, the actual negotiations will begin in November and the
sensitive question of removing tariffs will not be discussed
before 2001.
</P>
<P>
The main purpose of the current summit is to work out a
compromise on free trade in the hope that an agreement can be
reached on the issue, said Brazilian Foreign Minister Luis Felipe
Lampraia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
