<HEADLINE> Guangxi Launches Promotion to Attract Domestic Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 28 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region is using a convoy of motor vehicles to promote
tourism in coastal areas throughout east China.
</P>
<P>
The seven vehicles in the convoy are decorated with pictures
featuring Guangxi's natural landscape. The convoy arrived in
Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong Province, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi Deputy Chairman Yuan Fenglan accompanied the convoy to
Guangzhou and said that the region hopes the promotion campaign
aims at attracting more domestic tourists to Guangxi.
</P>
<P>
Yuan said the convoy will visit a dozen Chinese cities in
Guangdong, Fujian, Zhejiang, Jiangsu, Shanghai, Jiangxi and Hunan
provinces.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi features abundant tourism resources, including the
picturesque landscape in Guilin and a diversity of ethnic folk
traditions, as well as beautiful subtropical beaches along the
Beibu Gulf. The province also shares a border with Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region hosted 263,000 foreign tourists during
the first five months of this year, up 55 percent on last year's
same period. Tourism earnings grew by 42 percent on the previous
year's period to well over 67 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
A local tourism official said the region has witnessed a boom
in domestic tourism since the middle part of February this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
