<DOCNO> XIE19990628.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> United States Beat DPR Korea in Women's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
WASHINGTON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Hosts the United States needed
55 minutes to break the deadlock and went on to beat the DPR Korea
3-0 in the women's World Cup soccer tournament at Boston on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korean team, which needed a win to advance into the
quarterfinals, held the host team to a goalless draw after the first
55 minutes of the match.
</P>
<P>
But the Americans were obviously stronger both physically and
technically. They finally beat the DPR Korean team's defence line
at the 55th minute when Shannon MacMillan picked a cross in the left
and beat the DPR Korean goal-keeper with a sudden shot.
</P>
<P>
The Americans had a golden chance to enlarge the gap but
Kristine Lilly's shot hit the post.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korean team also missed a scoring chance as Kim Kum Sil
also hit the cross-bar.
</P>
<P>
After the 60th minute, the DPR Korean team were obviously tired
and could barely followed the pace of the host team. At the 68th
minute, Tisha Venturini headed home a cross to put the American team
2-0 ahead.
</P>
<P>
Eight minutes later, Venturini headed home again to seal the 3-0
victory for the host team.
</P>
<P>
The United States coach Tony DiCicco rest some of his top
players as they had already booked a berth in the quarterfinals.
They will play Group B runners-up Germany at Washington on June 30.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
