<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Greene Wins 200 Meters at U.S. Athletics Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Maurice Greene won the men's
200 meters but only after a surprising stumble at the start in the
U.S. athletics championships at Eugene, Oregon, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Greene clocked a wind-assisted 19.93 seconds despite slowing
down the last 10 meters. Rohsaan Griffin was second in 19.98 while
Kevin Little third in 20.19.
</P>
<P>
Greene, the 100-meter world record-holder, had to touch the
track with his left hand to balance himself after stumbling out of
the blocks.
</P>
<P>
Marion Jones triumphed in the women's 200 in 22.10 seconds,
followed by Latasha Jenkins who clocked 22.36. Inger Miller came
in third in 22.46.
</P>
<P>
John Godina produced the longest men's shot put in the world in
two years with a result of 22.02 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
