</P>
<P>
-- China's Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao yesterday called for a
greater effort to safeguard the development of the securities
market as it is an integral part of the country's socialist market
economy.
</P>
<P>
The securities market has played an active role in accelerating
China's economic development in the past few years and should be
used to support the reforms and development of state-owned
enterprises, Wen told a national meeting on the supervision and
regulation of futures and securities markets.
</P>
<P>
"China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- Government national accounts reflected a strong improvement
from January to May over the same period of last year, Minister of
Finance Xiang Huaicheng revealed Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Government at all levels had collected 415.7 billion yuan (50
billion US dollars) in revenue in the first five months, 24.9
percent higher than the same period of 1998 and also about 38.5
percent of the total revenue expected for this year.
</P>
<P>
-- After five days of discussions, the National People's
Congress (NPC) Standing Committee voted on Saturday morning in
Beijing to restrict a ruling by the Hong Kong Court of Final
Appeal granting the right of abode to children born in the
mainland to Hong Kong parents. 
