<HEADLINE> Li Na Wins Platform at Swedish Cup Diving Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese diver Li Na took the
women's platform title at the Swedish Cup international diving
meet in Ronneby, Sweden, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Li won with a total of 530.35 points despite her failure in a
difficult routine. Her compatriot Sang Xue won the silver at 497.
65.
</P>
<P>
The bronze medal went to Canada's Myriam Boileau, who collected
493.40.
</P>
<P>
Chinese divers also dominated the preliminaries for the men's 3-
meter springboard. Xiong Ni led with 416.75, followed by Chen
Yuzhou at 403.55.
</P>
<P>
The event will conclude on Tuesday. 
</P>
