<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Develops Seashore Ecology Tourism Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 28 (Xinhua) -- Tianjin, the largest port city in
north China, has invested 320 million yuan in recent years to
develop seashore tourism programs for its bathing beach.
</P>
<P>
The city completed the bathing beach, the country's largest man-
made seashore holiday resort, some 10 years ago on Bohai Bay. It
has so far attracted over 4.5 million visitors.
</P>
<P>
On the basis of the beach, the local tourism department has
constructed a 3,000-meter-long dam which helps form a three sq.km.
lake at high tide, and two beaches covering about one sq.km. each.
</P>
<P>
The department has also developed a series of tourism venues in
the area, including a heated swimming pool and an aquarium.
</P>
<P>
The city has planted 20,000 sq.m. of greenery in the beach area,
and weeping willows and flower gardens along the roads from the
beach to the city proper, thus forming an "ecological holiday
resort" as local people put it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
