<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, June 28 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA -- A draft cease-fire agreement was completed Sunday at
a officials meeting held in Zambian capital over the past few days
to make preparations for the Congo peace summit.
</P>
<P>
Zambian Presidential Affairs Minister Erick Silwamba said here
Sunday that the draft agreement is now being considered by defense
ministers, foreign ministers and home affairs ministers of the
regional countries. (Zambia-Draft-Ceasefire)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Greece's former dictator George Papadopoulos, who led
a military junta from 1967 to 1973, died in an Athens hospital on
Sunday at the age of 80.
</P>
<P>
Born in 1919, Papadopoulos was an army colonel when he seized
power in an April 1967 coup.
</P>
<P>
In December 1967, Papadopoulos took over as Prime Minister and
Defense Minister, and in 1973, he became President of Greece. (
Greece-Papadopoulos)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- Eight people, including a 15-year-old youth,
were shot and killed in different incidents in the KwaZulu-Natal
midlands of South Africa over the weekend, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police spokesman Captain Joshua Gwala said Sunday five of the
dead were from the Mpumulanga township near Pietermaritzburg. (
SAfrica-Murdering)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ATHENS -- Three NATO warships carrying troops and equipment for
peacekeeping duties in Kosovo arrived in the northern Greek port
of Thessaloniki on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
One Spanish warship disembarked 200 troops at the port while
two warships of France and Germany docked in the port with the
equipment and supplies such as military jeeps and armored
personnel carriers.
</P>
<P>
Another two Spanish vessels are expected to arrive in the port
later in the day.
</P>
<P>
Eight U.S. C-17 aircraft landed at the northern Macedonia
airport on Saturday night, with some 230 soldiers. (Greece-NATO)
</P>
