<DOCNO> XIE19990628.0243 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuban Women Win 1999 BCV Volleyball Masters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTREUX, Switzerland, June 27 (Xinhua) -- The Cuban women
became the champions of the 1999 BCV Volleyball Masters by
defeating the Chinese team in the final here Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic champions Cuba won 23-25, 25-19, 25-16, 25-17 to
repeat their feat at Atlanta in 1996, exploiting the injury of
star Chinese spiker Sun Yue in the second set.
</P>
<P>
The Olympic silver medalists China rallied from 9-13 down to
take the closely-combated first set 25-23.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, China and Cuba tied 14-all before captain
Sun collided with a Cuban player to injure her knees.
</P>
<P>
China, last year's runner-up here, suffered loss of both
attacking power and concentration after Sun was replaced and Cuba
apparently gained an upper hand through the rest of the match.
</P>
<P>
Doctors said Sun, who staggered back to hotel under the
assistance of two players after the game, would recover in several
days.
</P>
<P>
Altogether eight world leading women's volleyball teams
attended the yearly event from June 22-27, sponsored by BCV, a
Swiss cantonal bank.
</P>
<P>
In the match for the third place, Italy battled for five sets
to tame Brazil 25-16, 22-25, 17-25, 25-20, 29-27.
</P>
<P>
Russia was placed fifth after beating Canada while United
States finished seventh and Japan eighth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990628.0244 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nigeria Boost Hopes of Qualifying for World Cup Quar terfinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
WASHINGTON, June 27 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria fully recovered from a 7-1
defeat to the United States, beating Denmark 2-0 to boost their
chances of qualifying for the quarterfinals of the 3rd Women's World
Cup soccer tournament here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian team, which beat DPR Korea 2-1 and lost to hosts
the United States 7-1 in their previous two outings, opened the
scoring at the 24th minute when Akide Mercy completed a quick
counter-attack with a fierce shot.
</P>
<P>
The Danish team fought hard in the second half, put much pressure
on Nigerian defence. But their scoring ability turned them down.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerian team, which needed only a draw to secure a berth in
the quarterfinals, added one goal at the 80th minute when Nkiru
Okosieme took advantage of Danish defender's blunder and beat the
Danish goal-keeper.
</P>
<P>
The win put Nigeria on the second place with 6 points. The
United States have already qualified for the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
Now Nigeria pinned their qualifying hopes on the host team the
United States. If the American team beat or draw the DPR Korean team
in their last group match later on Sunday, then Nigeria will qualify.
</P>
<P>
If the DPR Korea upset the American at Boston, then they will
have six points, the same as the Nigerian team. The DPR Korean team
lost to Nigeria 2-1 and beat Denmark 3-1 in their previous group
matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
